															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/i-am-a-potato" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(215808); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=215808&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250819" alt="I Am A Potato" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=215808)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/i-am-a-potato" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(215808); return false;" >I Am A Potato</a></span> <span class="odate time_1225180334 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 Oct 2008 07:52</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-294401">
									

<p>See, that's the thing, the timing of everything, and your log just lays it all out so beautifully (Cain's cryptic message, recapturing Iris, the retrieval of Steel Doll, etc.) that I think it would just be better for me to place Wanderlust after it in continuity, and as such change those two characters.</p>
<p>Besides, the Steel Doll incident is cited at the beginning of Dr. Bishop's journal, and then <em>his</em> death is cited at the beginning of Wanderlust. So there's really no way to put those events before or else we get a nasty little temporal loop.</p>

							</div>

								
